There is a discussion of the assertion facility, and some suggestions about
appropriate and inappropriate usage, at
http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4/docs/guide/lang/assert.html.

In part, ...
The simple assertion facility does enable a limited form of
design-by-contract style programming. The assert statement is appropriate
for postcondition and class invariant checking. Precondition checking should
still be performed by checks inside methods that result in particular,
documented exceptions, such as IllegalArgumentException and
IllegalStateException. 



